HEADWORD: Nonconformity
<hw>Non*con*form"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Neglect or
failure of conformity; especially, in England, the neglect or refusal to
unite with the established church in its rites and modes of
worship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

